<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="213" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<bibRefCitation author="de Beaumont, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" pagination="211 - 238" publicationUrl="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" refId="B10" refString="de Beaumont, J, 1952a. Les Hoplisoides et les Psammaecius de la region palearctique (Hym. Sphecid). Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 25: 211 - 238, http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" title="Les Hoplisoides et les Psammaecius de la region palearctique (Hym. Sphecid)." url="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" volume="25" year="1952 a">De Beaumont (1952a</bibRefCitation>
: 223) changed the state of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Beaumont" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Gorytes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gorytes merceti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merceti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Gorytes merceti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de Beaumont to rank of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplisoides craverii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="craverii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Hoplisoides craverii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(A. Costa). As the only differences between these forms, he cited coloring features of the clypeus and legs. The study of the material from Spain, Russia (Crimea, Dagestan), Azerbaijan, Turkey, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan showed a high variability of these characteristics. We consider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Beaumont" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. merceti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="craverii" subSpecies="merceti">ssp. merceti</taxonomicName>
de Beaumont is only a color variation of a rather variable species with a range of color geographic forms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
